# The Docker build context for every service in docker-compose.prod.yml is the repo root
# (`context: ..`). django/worker only ever COPY MPCAutofill/ and docker/; nginx additionally COPYs
# frontend/ (but runs `npm install` fresh inside the build stage, never frontend/node_modules from the
# host). Everything below is unused by any of the three Dockerfiles, but was still being uploaded to
# the Docker daemon on every single build - node_modules alone is well over a gigabyte.
.git
frontend/node_modules
frontend/.next
frontend/out
frontend/test-results
frontend/playwright-report
frontend/playwright/.auth
image-cdn/node_modules
desktop-tool
github-release-reverse-proxy
cloudflare-static-site
schemas
.mypy_cache
.ruff_cache
test-results
